Section 9.  CoAP Header Compression with Proxies
================================================================

--- intro, after "The following refers to the origin client and origin
--- server as application endpoints." --- insert:
+ In terms of the SCHC architecture [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture], each
+ communication leg on which SCHC is used corresponds to a SCHC Session
+ between two SCHC Instances that share a common Context.  An entity
+ that performs SCHC on several legs, such as a proxy, hosts a SCHC
+ Instance for each such leg and terminates the corresponding Session;
+ SCHC-compressed data is never relayed as such across legs.

